CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 13, 1957, page B6, reads: "To Satisfy Buyers - Meat wrappers Clara Mancuso and Mary Coaters operate a super speed machine which cuts meats, wraps the cuts in plastic, identifies it, and weighs and prices it."
TitMainTitle: Meat wrappers Clara Mancuso and Mary Coaters wearing light colored dresses and aprons, working on assembly and packing for Loblaw's Grocery Store, in interior with stamps hanging in background and signs reading "it's the quality of of our work that counts" and "All packages must Look Good..."
